00:00:53.780 --> 00:00:55.530 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: How did you
get involved in doing

00:00:55.530 --> 00:00:56.945 align:middle line:90%
all of this for people?

00:00:56.945 --> 00:00:59.540 align:middle line:84%
>>PETERSON: I have worked
in the financial services

00:00:59.540 --> 00:01:02.000 align:middle line:90%
business for 30 years.

00:01:02.000 --> 00:01:04.700 align:middle line:10%
And every time I
worked with people,

00:01:04.700 --> 00:01:07.220 align:middle line:10%
I noticed that they would
be telling me something

00:01:07.220 --> 00:01:09.860 align:middle line:10%
very practical about
money, and I was also

00:01:09.860 --> 00:01:11.090 align:middle line:10%
feeling their energy.

00:01:11.090 --> 00:01:14.720 align:middle line:10%
And often that energy
was very fear oriented.

00:01:14.720 --> 00:01:17.240 align:middle line:84%
And it just caused me
to be super curious.

00:01:17.240 --> 00:01:19.760 align:middle line:84%
What's going on under
the surface of somebody's

00:01:19.760 --> 00:01:21.200 align:middle line:90%
relationship with money?

00:01:21.200 --> 00:01:24.040 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Why does
somebody need a helper?

00:01:24.040 --> 00:01:25.400 align:middle line:90%
>>PETERSON: Great question.

00:01:25.400 --> 00:01:29.740 align:middle line:84%
I think it's because we don't
realize the fear that we're

00:01:29.740 --> 00:01:30.790 align:middle line:90%
holding on to.

00:01:30.790 --> 00:01:34.900 align:middle line:84%
And one of the places that
fear comes out is with money.

00:01:34.900 --> 00:01:37.987 align:middle line:84%
And so it's really
hard to know, right?

00:01:37.987 --> 00:01:40.195 align:middle line:84%
It's just like your hand
right in front of your face.

00:01:40.195 --> 00:01:40.600 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Sure.

00:01:40.600 --> 00:01:41.808 align:middle line:90%
>>PETERSON: You can't see it.

00:01:41.808 --> 00:01:43.750 align:middle line:84%
And until someone brings
it to your attention,

00:01:43.750 --> 00:01:46.450 align:middle line:84%
you might not realize that
you're living a certain way,

00:01:46.450 --> 00:01:48.760 align:middle line:84%
yet there's so much
more potential for you.

00:01:48.760 --> 00:01:52.450 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: There is a phrase
called "scarcity mindset."

00:01:52.450 --> 00:01:54.497 align:middle line:90%
What does that mean?

00:01:54.497 --> 00:01:56.310 align:middle line:84%
>>PETERSON: Yeah,
it's a great question.

00:01:56.310 --> 00:01:58.120 align:middle line:84%
I think that it's
different for everybody.

00:01:58.120 --> 00:02:03.460 align:middle line:84%
The way I define it is a
zero-sum paradigm of life.

00:02:03.460 --> 00:02:06.670 align:middle line:84%
Meaning it's like we
treat life like it's a pie

00:02:06.670 --> 00:02:08.889 align:middle line:90%
and there's eight pieces.

00:02:08.889 --> 00:02:12.320 align:middle line:84%
And once the pieces are gone,
then there's nothing left.

00:02:12.320 --> 00:02:14.950 align:middle line:84%
So it's this idea of
there's not enough.

00:02:14.950 --> 00:02:16.340 align:middle line:90%
There's never enough.

00:02:16.340 --> 00:02:19.780 align:middle line:84%
I have found that not only
does that apply for the things

00:02:19.780 --> 00:02:21.475 align:middle line:90%
that we--

00:02:21.475 --> 00:02:25.540 align:middle line:84%
money, and supplies, or
resources, or toilet paper,

00:02:25.540 --> 00:02:27.940 align:middle line:84%
it also applies to how
we feel about ourselves

00:02:27.940 --> 00:02:29.265 align:middle line:90%
not being enough.

00:02:29.265 --> 00:02:32.720 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Should we be balancing
this in order to have enough?

00:02:32.720 --> 00:02:33.520 align:middle line:90%
>>PETERSON: Yeah.

00:02:33.520 --> 00:02:35.920 align:middle line:90%
And maybe explain your question.

00:02:35.920 --> 00:02:39.670 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Well let's say you chop
up this pie into eight pieces

00:02:39.670 --> 00:02:42.970 align:middle line:84%
like you just said and
all the pieces are gone.

00:02:42.970 --> 00:02:46.900 align:middle line:84%
How do you do it and keep
a piece or two in reserve?

00:02:46.900 --> 00:02:47.830 align:middle line:90%
>>PETERSON: Yeah.

00:02:47.830 --> 00:02:50.470 align:middle line:84%
Well that's the funny
thing is that it

00:02:50.470 --> 00:02:52.030 align:middle line:90%
isn't as simple as that.

00:02:52.030 --> 00:02:56.320 align:middle line:84%
And probably it is helpful to
talk about just the research

00:02:56.320 --> 00:02:57.550 align:middle line:90%
about scarcity.

00:02:57.550 --> 00:02:59.930 align:middle line:84%
This isn't just something
that we're making up.

00:02:59.930 --> 00:03:01.450 align:middle line:84%
There's been a lot
of research that

00:03:01.450 --> 00:03:05.590 align:middle line:84%
says that when we're living
with a scarcity mindset

00:03:05.590 --> 00:03:07.940 align:middle line:84%
or we feel like
there isn't enough,

00:03:07.940 --> 00:03:13.250 align:middle line:84%
we actually have a loss in IQ of
up to 14 points in that moment.

00:03:13.250 --> 00:03:17.660 align:middle line:84%
So it literally causes
us to tunnel our vision.

00:03:17.660 --> 00:03:20.410 align:middle line:84%
So instead of thinking
about all the possibilities

00:03:20.410 --> 00:03:22.840 align:middle line:84%
that are available
to us, we only

00:03:22.840 --> 00:03:26.620 align:middle line:84%
see a very small
portion of the options.

00:03:26.620 --> 00:03:28.600 align:middle line:90%
And so back to the pie.

00:03:28.600 --> 00:03:33.100 align:middle line:84%
We're treating life like a pie,
but in reality the potential

00:03:33.100 --> 00:03:33.970 align:middle line:90%
is limitless.

00:03:33.970 --> 00:03:36.250 align:middle line:90%
There's always tons of options.

00:03:36.250 --> 00:03:38.410 align:middle line:84%
But when we go to
a financial advisor

00:03:38.410 --> 00:03:41.410 align:middle line:84%
and they tell us that we don't
have enough money to retire,

00:03:41.410 --> 00:03:42.970 align:middle line:90%
we believe that.

00:03:42.970 --> 00:03:45.725 align:middle line:84%
And we shut down all
the other possibilities.

00:03:45.725 --> 00:03:47.350 align:middle line:84%
And that was one of
the problems that I

00:03:47.350 --> 00:03:51.310 align:middle line:84%
had working in the
business is I felt like we

00:03:51.310 --> 00:03:52.900 align:middle line:90%
were telling people lies.

00:03:52.900 --> 00:03:55.450 align:middle line:84%
We were telling them that
just because your money looks

00:03:55.450 --> 00:03:58.220 align:middle line:84%
one way today that's going
to be the rest of your life.

00:03:58.220 --> 00:03:59.990 align:middle line:90%
And that's simply not true.

00:03:59.990 --> 00:04:01.847 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And it's a
shocking not true,

00:04:01.847 --> 00:04:03.055 align:middle line:90%
isn't it for a lot of people?

00:04:03.055 --> 00:04:03.340 align:middle line:90%
>>PETERSON: Yeah.

00:04:03.340 --> 00:04:04.140 align:middle line:90%
Totally.

00:04:04.140 --> 00:04:05.290 align:middle line:90%
Especially right now.

00:04:05.290 --> 00:04:07.700 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Why retire
if you don't have to?

00:04:07.700 --> 00:04:09.075 align:middle line:84%
>>PETERSON: Yeah,
great question.

00:04:09.075 --> 00:04:10.120 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Yeah.

00:04:10.120 --> 00:04:13.390 align:middle line:84%
I plan to just keep
going until Tommy

00:04:13.390 --> 00:04:16.980 align:middle line:84%
comes back from a commercial
and says he's gone.

00:04:16.980 --> 00:04:18.519 align:middle line:90%
He's left us.

00:04:18.519 --> 00:04:19.600 align:middle line:90%
Why retire?

00:04:19.600 --> 00:04:20.720 align:middle line:90%
>>PETERSON: I agree.

00:04:20.720 --> 00:04:22.140 align:middle line:90%
I can't imagine life--

00:04:22.140 --> 00:04:23.150 align:middle line:90%
I love work.

00:04:23.150 --> 00:04:25.540 align:middle line:84%
I love making a
contribution and being

00:04:25.540 --> 00:04:27.380 align:middle line:90%
in service of other people.

00:04:27.380 --> 00:04:29.440 align:middle line:84%
I think that retirement,
with some idea

00:04:29.440 --> 00:04:33.160 align:middle line:84%
that maybe the financial
services came up with,

00:04:33.160 --> 00:04:34.905 align:middle line:84%
and we all just
said, OK, I guess

00:04:34.905 --> 00:04:36.280 align:middle line:84%
that's what we're
supposed to do.

00:04:36.280 --> 00:04:38.800 align:middle line:84%
But I think it also
has to do with the fact

00:04:38.800 --> 00:04:40.720 align:middle line:84%
that a lot of times,
people take jobs

00:04:40.720 --> 00:04:43.780 align:middle line:84%
and they work in jobs for their
whole life that aren't jobs

00:04:43.780 --> 00:04:44.860 align:middle line:90%
that they love.

00:04:44.860 --> 00:04:45.880 align:middle line:84%
And they can't wait
to get out of it.

00:04:45.880 --> 00:04:47.710 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Lots of unhappy
people out there.

00:04:47.710 --> 00:04:49.210 align:middle line:90%
Lots of them.

00:04:49.210 --> 00:04:51.790 align:middle line:84%
Gaia's "Missing Links"
program with Gregg Braden,

00:04:51.790 --> 00:04:56.350 align:middle line:84%
he discusses how we have been in
this model of fear and scarcity

00:04:56.350 --> 00:04:57.410 align:middle line:90%
for a long time.

00:04:57.410 --> 00:04:58.210 align:middle line:90%
Let's take a look.

00:04:58.210 --> 00:04:59.170 align:middle line:90%
[VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:04:59.170 --> 00:05:02.800 align:middle line:10%
- Now the current standard
model, it's based on a story

00:05:02.800 --> 00:05:05.020 align:middle line:10%
that you and I have been
steeped in from the time

00:05:05.020 --> 00:05:06.140 align:middle line:10%
that we were born.

00:05:06.140 --> 00:05:08.830 align:middle line:10%
It's the story of
Western civilization.

00:05:08.830 --> 00:05:12.550 align:middle line:10%
It is a story based upon
separation, competition,

00:05:12.550 --> 00:05:16.800 align:middle line:10%
conflict, struggle, scarcity.

00:05:16.800 --> 00:05:20.550 align:middle line:10%
It's the sterile sounding
story of a dead universe,

00:05:20.550 --> 00:05:23.190 align:middle line:10%
of random mutations
that just happened

00:05:23.190 --> 00:05:26.580 align:middle line:10%
as a result of just the
right conditions converging

00:05:26.580 --> 00:05:29.430 align:middle line:10%
at just the right time
in just the right way,

00:05:29.430 --> 00:05:33.570 align:middle line:10%
requiring a series of events
that are so lucky that even

00:05:33.570 --> 00:05:35.940 align:middle line:10%
scientists say it
takes an act of faith

00:05:35.940 --> 00:05:38.860 align:middle line:10%
to believe the story
that we're being told.

00:05:38.860 --> 00:05:41.280 align:middle line:84%
Well there's a new standard
model that's emerging.

00:05:41.280 --> 00:05:42.450 align:middle line:90%
It has to.

00:05:42.450 --> 00:05:45.270 align:middle line:10%
Because the evidence, the
science-based evidence

00:05:45.270 --> 00:05:47.820 align:middle line:10%
no longer supports
the scientific story,

00:05:47.820 --> 00:05:49.290 align:middle line:10%
the existing model.

00:05:49.290 --> 00:05:52.800 align:middle line:10%
In the new standard model,
it's a very different story.

00:05:52.800 --> 00:05:55.800 align:middle line:10%
It's the story of a
universe that is alive.

00:05:55.800 --> 00:05:57.550 align:middle line:10%
It's vibrant.

00:05:57.550 --> 00:06:01.140 align:middle line:10%
It's a story of a universe
where life is the rule rather

00:06:01.140 --> 00:06:03.300 align:middle line:10%
than the rare exception.

00:06:03.300 --> 00:06:07.110 align:middle line:10%
It's a story that creates a
model based upon cooperation,

00:06:07.110 --> 00:06:10.080 align:middle line:10%
not competition, upon
abundance, not scarcity,

00:06:10.080 --> 00:06:12.570 align:middle line:10%
upon mutual aid and
self-empowerment

00:06:12.570 --> 00:06:15.220 align:middle line:10%
through self-regulation.

00:06:15.220 --> 00:06:17.730 align:middle line:10%
And I want to stop right here
and just be very, very clear.

00:06:17.730 --> 00:06:19.590 align:middle line:10%
That is what this
series is all about.

00:06:19.590 --> 00:06:23.160 align:middle line:10%
You are learning about
your relationship

00:06:23.160 --> 00:06:24.240 align:middle line:10%
to the divine matrix.

00:06:24.240 --> 00:06:26.340 align:middle line:10%
You're learning about
your relationship

00:06:26.340 --> 00:06:29.070 align:middle line:10%
to the field that not
only connects all things,

00:06:29.070 --> 00:06:31.720 align:middle line:10%
it's the field that
makes you who you are.

00:06:31.720 --> 00:06:34.860 align:middle line:90%
You are emerging constantly.

00:06:34.860 --> 00:06:38.070 align:middle line:10%
Quanta is reemerging,
and reemerging,

00:06:38.070 --> 00:06:41.400 align:middle line:10%
and reemerging as the atoms
of your body from this field.

00:06:41.400 --> 00:06:44.270 align:middle line:10%
This is such a powerful
concept that we're not

00:06:44.270 --> 00:06:45.270 align:middle line:10%
separate from the field.

00:06:45.270 --> 00:06:46.620 align:middle line:10%
It is within us.

00:06:46.620 --> 00:06:48.840 align:middle line:10%
It is emerging as us.

00:06:48.840 --> 00:06:52.050 align:middle line:10%
And because we are part of,
rather than separate from, we

00:06:52.050 --> 00:06:55.110 align:middle line:10%
are given the ability
to self-regulate

00:06:55.110 --> 00:06:58.470 align:middle line:10%
how we relate to this field.

00:06:58.470 --> 00:07:01.140 align:middle line:10%
And we've just seen that
we're wired to do this.

00:07:01.140 --> 00:07:05.370 align:middle line:10%
Our biology is actually
designed perfectly

00:07:05.370 --> 00:07:10.480 align:middle line:10%
for specifically and exactly
this kind of self-regulation.

00:07:10.480 --> 00:07:13.140 align:middle line:10%
So the evidence that supports
these discoveries they're

00:07:13.140 --> 00:07:15.930 align:middle line:10%
telling us a new human story.

00:07:15.930 --> 00:07:18.310 align:middle line:10%
And I have to tell you
it is a beautiful story.

00:07:18.310 --> 00:07:20.020 align:middle line:10%
It is a powerful story.

00:07:20.020 --> 00:07:21.270 align:middle line:10%
It's a story of hope.

00:07:21.270 --> 00:07:23.430 align:middle line:10%
It's a story of
possibility based

00:07:23.430 --> 00:07:25.830 align:middle line:10%
in rock solid evidence
of the new science

00:07:25.830 --> 00:07:26.860 align:middle line:10%
and the new discoveries.

00:07:26.860 --> 00:07:27.660 align:middle line:90%
[END PLAYBACK]

00:07:27.660 --> 00:07:31.030 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Now Leisa, Gregg's
always an upbeat kind of guy.

00:07:31.030 --> 00:07:33.085 align:middle line:84%
But he did drop the
scarcity word there.

00:07:33.085 --> 00:07:34.210 align:middle line:90%
What did you think of that?

00:07:34.210 --> 00:07:35.010 align:middle line:90%
>>PETERSON: He did.

00:07:35.010 --> 00:07:36.960 align:middle line:90%
I love what he's talking about.

00:07:36.960 --> 00:07:41.610 align:middle line:84%
I love just feeling into
the possibility of what

00:07:41.610 --> 00:07:43.330 align:middle line:90%
we can create for ourselves.

00:07:43.330 --> 00:07:46.200 align:middle line:84%
And I think that's what is
really resonating in the work

00:07:46.200 --> 00:07:48.060 align:middle line:90%
that I do and what he's saying.

00:07:48.060 --> 00:07:52.260 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Do you teach people
to control their own destiny?

00:07:52.260 --> 00:07:53.280 align:middle line:90%
>>PETERSON: Yes.

00:07:53.280 --> 00:07:58.410 align:middle line:84%
But I like to think of it as
being the creator of the life

00:07:58.410 --> 00:07:59.850 align:middle line:90%
that they want to live.

00:07:59.850 --> 00:08:03.390 align:middle line:84%
I did not understand
that for much of my life.

00:08:03.390 --> 00:08:05.850 align:middle line:84%
I thought that you
worked really hard,

00:08:05.850 --> 00:08:07.110 align:middle line:90%
and you worked your way up.

00:08:07.110 --> 00:08:10.710 align:middle line:84%
And you followed the rules
to get to a certain place.

00:08:10.710 --> 00:08:12.990 align:middle line:84%
And I thought that
that was creating.

00:08:12.990 --> 00:08:15.600 align:middle line:84%
But what I have
since come to see

00:08:15.600 --> 00:08:19.110 align:middle line:84%
is that when we're playing
life by other people's rules,

00:08:19.110 --> 00:08:23.040 align:middle line:84%
we're really not creating what's
going to make us most happy.

00:08:23.040 --> 00:08:26.820 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: When events occur in
our lives, traumas, pandemics,

00:08:26.820 --> 00:08:30.840 align:middle line:84%
wars, health issues,
people that we care about

00:08:30.840 --> 00:08:37.890 align:middle line:84%
die, how does that affect our
ability to form our future?

00:08:37.890 --> 00:08:38.870 align:middle line:90%
What happens?

00:08:38.870 --> 00:08:40.673 align:middle line:84%
>>PETERSON: When
we face challenges

00:08:40.673 --> 00:08:41.840 align:middle line:90%
is what I'm hearing you say?

00:08:41.840 --> 00:08:43.090 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Every day, every day.

00:08:43.090 --> 00:08:45.140 align:middle line:84%
>>PETERSON: Every day
we face challenges.

00:08:45.140 --> 00:08:47.930 align:middle line:84%
I feel like they're
presenting us with a choice.

00:08:47.930 --> 00:08:52.370 align:middle line:84%
Are we going to feel like a
victim to those challenges?

00:08:52.370 --> 00:08:56.150 align:middle line:84%
Or are we going to see those
challenges as opportunities

00:08:56.150 --> 00:09:01.040 align:middle line:84%
to grow and expand into
something more than just

00:09:01.040 --> 00:09:04.890 align:middle line:84%
being constantly given a
challenge after challenge

00:09:04.890 --> 00:09:05.690 align:middle line:90%
after challenge?

00:09:05.690 --> 00:09:08.130 align:middle line:84%
Because those challenges
don't ever go away.

00:09:08.130 --> 00:09:09.920 align:middle line:84%
It's what you're
going to do with them.

00:09:09.920 --> 00:09:11.780 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Give us
some examples of how

00:09:11.780 --> 00:09:15.200 align:middle line:84%
this scarcity mindset
has affected some people

00:09:15.200 --> 00:09:16.350 align:middle line:90%
throughout the ages.

00:09:16.350 --> 00:09:17.600 align:middle line:90%
>>PETERSON: Yeah.

00:09:17.600 --> 00:09:22.640 align:middle line:84%
So scarcity leads
